theorem Topology.closure_inter_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (closure A ∩ closure B : Set X) = closure A ∩ closure B := by
  -- Both `closure A` and `closure B` are closed, hence so is their intersection.
  have hClosed : IsClosed (closure A ∩ closure B : Set X) :=
    (isClosed_closure (s := A)).inter (isClosed_closure (s := B))
  -- We prove equality via two inclusions.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First, show `closure (closure A ∩ closure B)` is contained in the intersection.
    intro x hx
    have hxA : x ∈ closure A := by
      -- `closure A ∩ closure B` is contained in `closure A`.
      have hsubset : (closure A ∩ closure B : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
        intro y hy; exact hy.1
      exact (closure_mono hsubset) hx
    have hxB : x ∈ closure B := by
      -- `closure A ∩ closure B` is contained in `closure B`.
      have hsubset : (closure A ∩ closure B : Set X) ⊆ closure B := by
        intro y hy; exact hy.2
      exact (closure_mono hsubset) hx
    exact And.intro hxA hxB
  · -- The reverse inclusion follows from the universal inclusion `s ⊆ closure s`.
    intro x hx
    exact (subset_closure : (closure A ∩ closure B : Set X) ⊆
        closure (closure A ∩ closure B)) hx
